{"name":"Solton Officer","size":"large","type":"Humanoid/Beast","tag":"Harport Colonial/Warhorse","alignment":"neutral good","hitDice":"6","armorName":"chain mail","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":1,"otherArmorDesc":"12","speed":"50","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"0","customHP":false,"customSpeed":true,"hpText":"45 (6d10 + 12)","speedDesc":"80 ft. mounted, 30 ft standing.","strPoints":"18","dexPoints":"14","conPoints":"14","intPoints":"9","wisPoints":"13","chaPoints":"11","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"0","telepathy":0,"cr":"2","customCr":"2 (450 XP)","customProf":2,"isLegendary":false,"legendariesDescription":"The centaur can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The centaur regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the centaur can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the centaur can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The centaur can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":false,"mythicDescription":"If the centaur's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using {Some Ability}.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the centaur's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the centaur dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Charge","desc":"If [MON] moves at least 30 ft. straight toward a target and then hits it with a pike attack on the same turn, the target takes an extra 4 (1d6) piercing damage and cannot take reactions until the end of it's next turn."},{"name":"Mounted","desc":"[MON] can be knocked off his horse with a contested athletics check. While unmounted he cannot use charge."}],"actions":[{"name":"Pike","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ +6 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. _Hit:_ 9 (1d10 + 4) piercing damage."},{"name":"Javelin","desc":"_Ranged Weapon Attack:_ +6 to hit, range 30/120ft., one target. _Hit:_ 8 (1d6 + 4) piercing damage."},{"name":"Remount","desc":"[MON] calls and remounts his horse, this movement provokes opportunity attacks.\nA contest animal handling check may disrupt this action."}],"bonusActions":[{"name":"Polearm Master","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ +6 to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. _Hit:_ 5 (1d4 + 4) piercing damage."}],"reactions":[],"legendaries":[],"mythics":[],"lairs":[],"regionals":[],"sthrows":[{"name":"str","order":0}],"skills":[{"name":"athletics","stat":"str"},{"name":"intimidation","stat":"cha"},{"name":"religion","stat":"int"}],"damagetypes":[],"specialdamage":[],"conditions":[],"languages":[{"name":"Common","speaks":true}],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"","pluralName":"","doubleColumns":false,"separationPoint":2,"damage":[]}